                "name": "Elinore"
            },
            "reviewBody": "These are one of the first things I made by myself as a kid. Must have been 8 or so. There was a recipe for them in a sesame street cookbook. I've made them many times since. Truthfully, I still make and serve a few things from that book. I don't always tell my guests though."
        },
        {
            "@type": "Review",
            "author": {
                "@type": "Person",
                "name": "Highway_12"
            },
            "reviewBody": "I found the temperature too high for my oven - the meringues browned, which I was hoping to avoid."
        },
        {
            "@type": "Review",
            "author": {
                "@type": "Person",
                "name": "Laura"
            },
            "reviewBody": "These were really tasty, though I found them a little too sweet. Next time I might bump the sugar down just a titch, but great otherwise :)"
        },
        {
            "@type": "Review",
            "author": {
                "@type": "Person",
                "name": "EK"
            },
            "reviewBody": "I was thinking what to do with left over egg whites after making Zabaglione the other day, and I decided to make meringue cookies. I used to have white plane meringue cookies, but I've never tried meringue with chocolate chips. It came out really tasty and my family liked it a lot as well. I'll definitely make these again! Thank you very much!"
        },
        {
            "@type": "Review",
            "author": {
                "@type": "Person",
                "name": "Audrey G"
            },
            "reviewBody": "Just made these-- they turned out really excellently! My baking time went by pretty quickly, just an hour and a half. They're very light and not tooo terribly sweet as I find meringues can often be. Thanks SE!"
        }
